---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy - JSON Formatter Pro: Secure & Private"
  description="JSON Formatter Pro is a private, client-side JSON formatter. Your JSON is processed entirely in your browser and never transmitted to any server. No tracking, no data collection."
  path="/privacy"
  keywords="private JSON formatter, secure JSON tool, client-side formatter, no server JSON tool, privacy policy, data security"
>
  <article class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 py-12 text-sm text-subtle">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-semibold text-fg">Privacy</h1>
    <p class="mt-3">
      JSON Formatter Pro is a client-side tool. Any JSON you paste, type, upload, or drop into the editor
      is processed entirely in your browser. It is never uploaded to any server, and no analytics events
      contain your content.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-8 text-base font-semibold text-fg">What is stored locally</h2>
    <ul class="mt-2 list-disc space-y-1 pl-6">
      <li>Your last input (up to 512 KB) so the editor restores when you return.</li>
      <li>Your formatting preferences: indentation, transforms, selected view, and theme.</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="mt-2">
      These live in your browser's <code>localStorage</code> under the key
      <code>json-formatter-pro</code>. Clearing your browser storage removes them completely.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-8 text-base font-semibold text-fg">Network requests</h2>
    <p class="mt-2">
      Once the page is loaded, JSON Formatter Pro makes no network requests with your content.
      No third-party scripts, fonts, or trackers are loaded at runtime.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-8 text-base font-semibold text-fg">Analytics</h2>
    <p class="mt-2">
      If enabled by the site operator, Cloudflare Web Analytics may be used for aggregate, cookieless page
      view counts. It does not receive your JSON content and does not identify individual users.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-8 text-base font-semibold text-fg">Advertising & Third-Party Services</h2>
    <p class="mt-2">
      JSON Formatter Pro may display advertisements through Google AdSense or other advertising partners. These partners may:
    </p>
    <ul class="mt-2 list-disc space-y-1 pl-6">
      <li>Use cookies and similar tracking technologies to serve ads based on your browsing activity</li>
      <li>Collect information about your visits to display personalized ads</li>
      <li>Use Google Analytics for analytics purposes</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="mt-2">
      You can control ad personalization through your Google Ads Settings at <a href="https://adssettings.google.com" class="text-primary hover:underline" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">adssettings.google.com</a>.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-8 text-base font-semibold text-fg">Cookies</h2>
    <p class="mt-2">
      JSON Formatter Pro uses cookies for:
    </p>
    <ul class="mt-2 list-disc space-y-1 pl-6">
      <li><strong>Functional:</strong> Theme preference, localStorage persistence (retained indefinitely until user clears)</li>
      <li><strong>Analytics:</strong> Cloudflare Web Analytics (non-identifying, aggregate only)</li>
      <li><strong>Advertising:</strong> Google AdSense and advertising partner cookies (retained per their policies, typically 13 months)</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="mt-2">
      You can disable cookies in your browser settings. Note that disabling cookies may affect tool functionality.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-8 text-base font-semibold text-fg">Data Retention</h2>
    <p class="mt-2">
      <strong>Browser Storage:</strong> Your formatter input and preferences are retained in browser localStorage until you manually clear them.
    </p>
    <p class="mt-2">
      <strong>Analytics Data:</strong> Cloudflare Web Analytics data is retained in accordance with Cloudflare's privacy practices.
    </p>
    <p class="mt-2">
      <strong>Google AdSense Cookies:</strong> Retained per Google's policies, typically 13 months from last activity.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-8 text-base font-semibold text-fg">GDPR & User Rights (EU/EEA Users)</h2>
    <p class="mt-2">
      If you are located in the European Union or European Economic Area, you have the following rights:
    </p>
    <ul class="mt-2 list-disc space-y-1 pl-6">
      <li><strong>Right to Access:</strong> You can request a copy of your personal data</li>
      <li><strong>Right to Rectification:</strong> You can correct inaccurate data</li>
      <li><strong>Right to Erasure:</strong> You can request deletion of your data</li>
      <li><strong>Right to Restrict Processing:</strong> You can limit how your data is used</li>
      <li><strong>Right to Portability:</strong> You can obtain your data in a portable format</li>
      <li><strong>Right to Object:</strong> You can object to processing for marketing purposes</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="mt-2">
      To exercise these rights, contact us at hashcode.dev@gmail.com.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-8 text-base font-semibold text-fg">CCPA Rights (California Users)</h2>
    <p class="mt-2">
      If you are a California resident, the California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA) grants you the right to:
    </p>
    <ul class="mt-2 list-disc space-y-1 pl-6">
      <li>Know what personal information is being collected</li>
      <li>Know whether your personal information is sold or disclosed</li>
      <li>Say no to the sale or sharing of your personal information</li>
      <li>Access your personal information</li>
      <li>Request deletion of information</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="mt-2">
      To exercise CCPA rights, contact us at hashcode.dev@gmail.com.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-8 text-base font-semibold text-fg">Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
    <p class="mt-2">
      We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of changes by posting the new Privacy Policy on this page and updating the "Last updated" date.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-8 text-base font-semibold text-fg">Contact</h2>
    <p class="mt-2">
      Questions about this privacy policy or your data? Contact us at:
    </p>
    <ul class="mt-2 list-disc space-y-1 pl-6">
      <li><strong>Email:</strong> hashcode.dev@gmail.com</li>
      <li><strong>Support:</strong> <a href="/contact" class="text-primary hover:underline">Contact Us</a></li>
    </ul>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
